SIMPLE: echo
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Echo
<hw>Ech"o</hw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧k"⟦osl⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Echoes</plw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧k"⟦omac⟧z)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>echo</ets>, Gr. <grk>'hchw`</grk> echo, sound, akin to
<grk>'hchh`</grk>, <grk>'h^chos</grk>, sound, noise; cf. Skr.
<ets>v⟦amac⟧⟦cced⟧</ets> to sound, bellow; perh. akin to E.
<ets>voice</ets>: cf. F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧cho</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A sound reflected from an opposing surface and repeated to the ear
of a listener; repercussion of sound; repetition of a sound.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The babbling <qex>echo</qex> mocks the hounds.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The woods shall answer, and the <qex>echo</qex> ring.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: Sympathetic recognition; response;
answer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fame is the <qex>echo</qex> of actions, resounding them.</q>
<rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Many kind, and sincere speeches found an <qex>echo</qex> in his
heart.</q> <rj><qau>R. L. Stevenson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <sd>(a)</sd> <fld>(Myth. & Poetic)</fld> <def>A wood or
mountain nymph, regarded as repeating, and causing the reverberation of
them.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sweet <qex>Echo</qex>, sweetest nymph, that liv'st unseen⟦br⟧
Within thy airy shell.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj></p>

<p><sd>(b)</sd> <fld>(Gr. Myth.)</fld> <def>A nymph, the daughter of Air
and Earth, who, for love of Narcissus, pined away until nothing was left
of her but her voice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Compelled me to awake the courteous <qex>Echo</qex>⟦br⟧
To give me answer from her mossy couch.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Whist, Contract Bridge)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A
signal, played in the same manner as a trump signal, made by a player
who holds four or more trumps (or as played by some exactly three
trumps) and whose partner has led trumps or signaled for trumps.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A signal showing the number held of a plain suit when
a high card in that suit is led by one's partner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Echo organ</b></col> <fld>(Mus.)</fld>, <cd>a set organ
pipes inclosed in a box so as to produce a soft, distant effect; --
generally superseded by the swell.</cd> -- <col><b>Echo stop</b></col>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld>, <cd>a stop upon a harpsichord contrived for producing
the soft effect of distant sound.</cd> -- <col><b>To applaud to the
echo</b></col>, <cd>to give loud and continuous applause.</cd>
<rj><au>M. Arnold.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I would <qex>applaud</qex> thee <qex>to the very echo</qex>,⟦br⟧
That should applaud again.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Echo</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Echo
<hw>Ech"o</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Echoed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Echoing</conjf>. -- <pos>3d pers. sing. pres.</pos>
<conjf>Echoes</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To send
back (a sound); to repeat in sound; to reverberate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Those peals are <qex>echoed</qex> by the Trojan throng.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The wondrous sound⟦br⟧
Is <qex>echoed</qex> on forever.</q> <rj><qau>Keble.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To repeat with assent; to respond; to
adopt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They would have <qex>echoed</qex> the praises of the men whom they
envied, and then have sent to the newspaper anonymous libels upon
them.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Echo</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Echo
<hw>Ech"o</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To give an echo; to resound; to be
sounded back; <as>as, the hall <ex>echoed</ex> with
acclamations</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Echoing</xex> noise.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Blackmore.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Echoer</ent>⟦br⟧
